76561198357151444,Recommended,244430,31547602,Posted: 4 May,all,deelwurf,"Absolutely loved this game!  Only ever played Myst before on really bad ports of the original (which there seem to be an abundance of).  This game allows you to play in ""classic"" and ""freeroam"" mode.  I found ""classic"" mode with Move Speed set to the highest value was a good approximation of the original thing (but with much better graphics).I was actually quite surprised by how not difficult and short of a game this was.  The puzzles are very cryptic but once you start to understand how the developers think it's really not that hard.  Everything you need to do is literally spelled out for you.  I found Day of the Tentacle to be a much harder game.  The keys to success in Myst are simple:  Read and Observe.There is some thinking outside of the box at times.  It may be tempting to try ""brute forcing"" your way through puzzles but that is not how the game was meant to be played (there is only one place I know of where this is required and takes forever in this version).  There was one puzzle where I wrote a program to simulate it's behavior and tested all possible combination in the simulations just to learn the way I was approaching it would never solve!  So be warned about brute forcing!From what I can tell there are no closing credits.  I had beat the game and spent a little bit of time trying to figure out what to do next.  I can't really say much more about this without spoiling anything.  Great game though and highly recommended/required for anybody who calls themselves a ""nerd."""
