76561198028066825,Recommended,244430,9073075,"Posted: 12 February, 2014",all,Brassman,"This review was negative when the game launched, due to several issues with game optimization.  A patch on February 27 corrected most of these errors, and the game behind them is the same MYST as always.Now that this game is far more likely to run on your system, the question left is whether or not you should buy this instead of the first RealMYST. I believe it is a matter of preference. RealMYST runs almost perfectly fluid and costs less than half the price of the masterpiece edition.  On the other hand, this modern update boasts new textures, lighting effects and post processing effects that can make the gameworld seem more alive. Despite these improvements, the masterpiece edition's textures are still noticeably bad by modern standards (particularly the leaves on trees). The game still appears to require more resources than one might think necessary to run smoothly.Ultimately I think whether these improvements are worth the cost is a question best left to you. The game is playable now, and I will honor my original statement and recommend it."
