,Recommended,244430,16461742,"Posted: 16 June, 2015",all,Tossing Ankle High Rocket Sauce,"realMyst is a graphically updated of the 1993 Cyan game Myst.  Myst is a puzzle game where you play as a character whom we don't know the name of, and we are given virtually no backstory.  But by going to different 'ages' through books and solving puzzles, more and more of the truth is revealed.  I won't give any major plot spoilers for those who want to really want to invest themselves in finding out the story, but for those who want just a bit of backstory, here you go:The background of your own character is unknown and there is no way of finding out who you are immediately.  You stumble upon a note from a man named Atrus.  Atrus writes ""linking books,"" which are books used to travel between different ages.  Atrus has a wife, Catherine, whom we don't meet, and two sons, Sirrus and Achenar.  Sirrus and Achenar are each trapped in linking books, and they want your help to get out, but there is a catch:  They each say that the other brother is not to be trusted.  They each say that Atrus met a terrible fate at the hands of the other brother.  It is up to the player to uncover the truth.Overall, this game gets a 10/10 from me, it excells in every single aspect that puzzle games should have.  Everyone will love this game, even though it can be frustrating at times.  Enjoy!"
