,Recommended,244430,8999112,"Posted: 6 February, 2014",all,WildKarrde,"http://youtu.be/W79CC2EW4voMyst was first released to critical acclaim in 1993, 21 years ago! Seven years later, in 2000, RealMyst was released. A game that took the slideshow world of Myst and turned it into a living, breathing real 3D game world. Now, 14 years later, in 2014, comes RealMyst Masterpiece Edition! Some say that this is just a cheap port, others say it's a money grab. The truth of the matter is that it is an entirely new engine, built from the ground up, to give us the greatest version of Myst ever created. Not only does this game include graphical updates, but the control system is much better as well. No, it's not the most graphically advanced came of the decade, but it's advanced enough that old fans will appreciate it, and new fans will be born from it.If you have been a fan of the Myst series for the last 20 years, this is a great platform to revisit the world from. If you are new to the Myst world, be aware, this game is probably unlike anything else you have seen. There are no tutorials, and the storyline is a mystery for most of the game. The visuals are exciting and the puzzles are mystifying. This game is entirely about the journey, not the end. So enjoy it while it lasts.This video is for those of you like me, who loved the original RealMyst, but want to see how it really stacks up to the newest version of the game.Here is another video that compares the original 1993 Myst to RealMyst Masterpiece. The photo's are available in-game when you use the classic control mode, and press the shift key.http://youtu.be/Na81ftiGHx0"
