76561197971877162,Recommended,244430,8992127,"Posted: 5 February, 2014",all,Asses of Fire,"I grew up playing the original and the ability to walk around myst island with improved graphics is just amazing.  Cyan did a fantastic job with this remake of the realmyst game from 2001 or so. If you love myst then you should fall in love with this version.Summary:In Myst you play an unknown traveller that finds a book somewhere (you don't find this out until you read the Myst novel's.)  Once you open its cover, you are transported to Myst Island.  Once there, the player discovers the lore of the D'ni and how they created links to worlds that already existed in other dimensions through the use of ""The Art.""The Art is a way of creating linking books to other worlds.  You, the player, are in one of those worlds.  Myst Island is a refuge for Atrus and his family.  Through reading the books in the Myst library, you discover everything about Atrus' sons and gain some insight into his travels in other worlds.in Myst, you must solve a way to get back to your world.  From reading certain notes spread thoughout the island and in other worlds, you discover a plot to imprison Atrus and leave him for dead by his wicked sons, Sirrus and Achenar.Conclusion:For its day, Myst was an amazing game and truly the first of its kind on CD-ROM.  Each indidual screen was created on a mac and each time the player clicked forward, they would move to the next pre-rendered screen.  Now, you can move all around freely.  realMyst ME is the definitive edition for the original Myst game.Keep an eye out for the starry expanse project too.  It's a small dev team remaking RIven in Unreal 4.  Riven is the sequel to Myst.  If you've never tried it, at least play the original Riven.  You will feel immersed in both games because there is just so much lore to be found in both."
