,Recommended,244430,13679938,"Posted: 28 December, 2014",all,EnduringBeta,"It's basically impossible to capture what was so amazing about the original Myst in 1993. These re-releases show that to me. But it can be nice to revisit the old island, check out how the spaceship is doing. See if that giant cog is still there, if that boiler still works.Moving around independently is nice, but adds little beyond seeing places previously rendered in still images from the occasional new angle. The updated graphics leave something to be desired. The game feels torn between being locked into its small levels from the 90s and expressing its beauty with the technology of today. In this way it begins to feel out of place, odd. For another example, the video of the brothers trapped in their books is painfully low-quality (understandably so!), and the ""distortion"" effect, reminiscent of VHS degradation or antenna tuning, shows its age.Part of what makes the appeal of the original Myst so unattainable is that I, we, are different people now. Not only was I extremely young and exploring a fantasy world for the first time, but in 20 years we've seen what games are capable of. We've explored amazing worlds with hidden stories and mysterious origins. Time and video gaming has moved on, and while Myst will be remembered for its landmark status at the time, it, like early 3D games, will be less playable going forward.I enjoyed the additional age after beating the game. It was a nice epilogue to the original. I liked that there was an internal help system for those who might need it. I felt it could have been implemented better, just like the controls, which I never fully got used to. But the additional feature is nice.I'm not sure if I recommend this generally. It's often really cheap, so there's little cost to getting it. If you want to relive a shadow, if a crisp, well-defined and anti-aliased shadow, of the original experience, get it. Don't expect magic, though.Hmm. It appears I HAVE to either recommend or not. I imagined this without a thumbs-up or -down. But given the price and the frequency it's on sale, it's an okay buy.(I wrotea more personal and sprawling review of this gameon my website.)"
